-- U.K.'s FTSE 100 Index Retreats Most in Six Months on Greek Debt Concern
-- Andrew Rummer
-- 2010-04-27T15:42:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/u-k-s-ftse-100-index-retreats-most-in-six-months-on-greek-debt-concern.html

          
          
             U.K. stocks sank the most in six
months as Standard & Poor’s cut Greece’s credit ratings to junk,
spurring concern the nation is moving closer to default.  
 The FTSE 100 Index slid 2.6 percent to 5,603.52, the
biggest drop since November.  
          
          


  


        